Author: immersive
Title: [ANN] ImmersiveOS - mixed reality platform powered by blockchain
Body: We are a distributed dev team of blockchain and 3d developers, dreamers and product designers. We are very excited to announce this project today and to be able to share it with the [Suspicious link removed]munity.  We are looking for feedback on our white-paper which discusses how rapid recent innovation in blockchain tech can empower new kind of mixed reality interactive experiences.  We also welcome anyone who shares our vision for a blockchain powered augmented reality activities to contact us directly and explore collaborating with us on this new project. We have several open development grants published on our site and more are being added.  Web: https://immersiveos.com Whitepaper: https://immersiveos.com/whitepaper.html Contact information: available on our site.  Thanks!

Author: taxmanmt5
Title: [ANN] ImmersiveOS - mixed reality platform powered by blockchain
Body: I am not fully on the same spot as you with understanding this one.  Let me compare it to Windows for example, since it is being branded an OS.  Windows, since Vista I think, stores most of the information in meta packages for a lot of tasks and the main job of the OS is to grab that information, use it in a way that is specific to the task at hand and give back returns.
